tafsir[3]{c,v,t}:
  16,17,"(Is He then Who createth) Allah (as him who createth not?) as him who cannot create: i.e. idols. (Will ye not then remember?) will you not take heed in that which Allah has created for you?"
  16,19,"(And Allah knoweth that which ye keep hidden) of good or evil (and that which ye proclaim) of good or evil."
  16,24,"(And when it is said unto them) to those who were later killed in the valley of Badr: (What hath your Lord revealed?) What does Muhammad (pbuh) say to you on behalf of your Lord? (they say: (Mere) fables of the men of old) the mere lies and tales of the people of old."